{"questionId":"2948741","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>You may assume that the total area, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>, of the region between the graph <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis can be written as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>∞</mo></msubsup><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math> and is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>b</mi></msubsup><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>120</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The <em><strong>M1</strong></em> can be awarded if either part (d)(i) or part (d)(ii) is correct.<br><br></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2948741","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.1dii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"A5.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.11—Definite integrals, areas under curve onto x-axis and areas between curves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
